<!-- Node: "Code Locks in Half-Life" -->
<div class="body_box_header">Code Locks in Half-Life</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/2" title="View user profile.">Gard</a> on Monday, June 7, 2004 - 20:05</small><br /><br />
Sebastiannielsen has just posted a tutorial on the RUST website called <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/book/view/290">Code Locks</a>. Several techniques exist to make doors with code locks, but I think this is by far the easiest and most exciting method todate. Sebastiannielsen points out that the code locks will be cool in multiplayer maps, where the developer can have a "code" to enter a protect-room (full with weapons). Imagine a button to open a door with lava under all the other players. Why not a turret or use your imagination! Check out Sebastiannielsen's <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/book/view/290">Code Lock Tutorial</a>
<br /><br />
<a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/login" >Login</a> or <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/register" >Register</a> to post comments &middot; <a href="http://assets.aq2world.com/archive/websites/www.gamedesign.net/node/view/293" title="Read the rest of this posting." class="read-more"><b>Read more</b></a>
</div><br />


<!-- Node: "Human Head Studios Hiring" -->
<div class="body_box_header">Human Head Studios Hiring</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/2157" title="View user profile.">method</a> on Monday, June 7, 2004 - 19:06</small><br /><br />
Human Head Studios, Incorporated is looking for an animator to add to their collection of heads.  This is a full time, on-site position with benefits for a project using the DOOM 3 Engine.<br><br>

In order to be considered for this job, they require that you be able to demonstrate the following:<br><br>

1. Thorough understanding of animation fundamentals<br>including posing, timing, and character weight.<br>
2. Be able to rig character models for animation<br>
3. Working technical knowledge of Maya Animator.<br>
4. Willing to accept direction and work well under pressure.<br>
5. Self motivated and a desire to work with a team.
<br /><br />
